Source: OIE alert messages, 17 Jun 2004 [edited]
<http://oie.int/Messages/040617LSO.htm>

African horse sickness (AHS) in Lesotho in April 2004
---------------------------------------------------
(Date of previous outbreak of African horse sickness in Lesotho reported to
the OIE: March 1998).
The monthly report of Lesotho for April 2004, received from Dr Malefane
Moleko, Chief Veterinary Officer, Department of Livestock and Veterinary
Services, Ministry of Agriculture and Marketing, Maseru, indicates the
occurrence of 2 outbreaks of AHS in Lesotho in April 2004.
Location of the outbreaks: Maseru (29 deg 33 min S, 28 deg 23 min E) and
Qacha's Nek (30 deg 15 min S, 28 deg 65 min E).
Total number of cases: 23.
Total number of deaths: 2.
The monthly report of Lesotho for May 2004 indicates the absence of any new
outbreak of AHS.
--
